Title: Cars 3 - Official US Trailer
Comment:
Woah... did anybody else get the vibe that this is a semi-autobiographical story about Pixar itself? A car that once couldn't lose, then gets swept up in promotion, bottom lines, and is mandated to play it safe to maintain legacy- "Every time you lose, you damage yourself". We see that the times have changed- he can't keep doing the same thing- the competition is getting better, faster and flashier, but he "can be smarter". Then realizes that the reward isn't the "stuff", it's the race- the reason they started in the first place.

I'm not really a fan of the the Cars movies, but this one feels like Pixar has something to say. Let's have it, fellas.
